85.7	Partition_of_India	Partition of India	The Partition of India , (Nastaliq) ) was the partition of British India on the basis of religious demographics. This led to the creation of the sovereign states of the Dominion of Pakistan (later the Islamic Republic of Pakistan) and the Union of India (later Republic of India) which took place in 1947, on August 14th and 15th, respectively.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3c/Partition_of_India-en.svg/220px-Partition_of_India-en.svg.png
